Monday night football will see Manchester United host Arsenal at Old Trafford. With only two wins in their last 12 Premier League matches, Ole Gunnar Solskjaer is under pressure to start producing results. The Gunners, however, are in fourth place and will be looking to take advantage of United’s striker crisis. Kick-off is 8 pm West African time. Man United XI vs Arsenal: De Gea, Tuanzebe, Lindelof, Maguire, Young, McTominay, Pogba, Pereira, Lingard, James, Rashford Arsenal XI vs Man United: Leno, Chambers, Sokratis, Luiz, Kolasinac, Guendouzi, Xhaka, Torreira, Pepe, Saka, Aubameyang Monday, September 28
